801
01:03:19,086 --> 01:03:22,131
How in the world
can Da-jeong stand seeing his face?

802
01:03:22,715 --> 01:03:23,883
He's going to hear you.

803
01:03:27,220 --> 01:03:28,346
I don't care.

804
01:03:37,104 --> 01:03:38,564
Enjoy.

805
01:03:38,648 --> 01:03:41,025
-Can you get me one more of this?
-Sure.

806
01:05:11,490 --> 01:05:12,825
Will you accept this rose?

807
01:05:13,659 --> 01:05:15,912
It's a paper rose. It won't wither,

808
01:05:15,995 --> 01:05:17,914
it's not prickly, and it's recyclable.

809
01:05:17,997 --> 01:05:20,499
You could also jot things down on it.

810
01:05:20,583 --> 01:05:22,877
YONGSAN STATION, 99, 7641

811
01:05:22,960 --> 01:05:25,254
Do you like music boxes?
Should we go get one?

812
01:05:25,338 --> 01:05:28,090
Did he ever tell you about his childhood?

813
01:05:28,174 --> 01:05:30,259
On March 13, 2003 at 9 p.m.,

814
01:05:30,843 --> 01:05:32,887
I killed Kim Myeong-ja.

815
01:05:32,970 --> 01:05:34,055
Now,

816
01:05:34,138 --> 01:05:37,224
I'm putting an end to everything.

817
01:07:21,287 --> 01:07:24,081
It was nothing to be scared about.

818
01:07:24,165 --> 01:07:26,792
Actually, it was like having a lollipop.

819
01:07:26,876 --> 01:07:29,045
If I say I'm curious about you,

820
01:07:29,128 --> 01:07:30,963
can you understand that?

821
01:07:31,047 --> 01:07:34,633
…a memory to painful to think about,

822
01:07:34,717 --> 01:07:35,885
what do you say?

823
01:07:35,968 --> 01:07:39,346
You know that
I can help you anytime. Right?

824
01:07:39,430 --> 01:07:42,641
I know this sounds crazy,
but I think I know who this is.

825
01:07:42,725 --> 01:07:46,145
I showed him
your photo from middle school.

826
01:07:46,228 --> 01:07:47,772
Don't run away.

827
01:07:47,855 --> 01:07:51,192
She makes me
fold the world in half and run to her.

828
01:07:51,275 --> 01:07:55,905
Subtitle translation by: Soo-ji Kim

